helm create helm_chart_nginx

cd helm_chart_nginx

Create Chart.yaml

apiVersion: v2
name: helm_chart_nginx
description: A Helm chart for deploying NGINX
version: 0.1.0

Create values.yaml

replicaCount: 1
image:
  repository: nginx
  tag: latest
  pullPolicy: IfNotPresent


Now we need to create Templates in which we will create deployment.yaml

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: {{ include "nginx-chart.fullname" . }}
  labels:
    app: nginx
spec:
  replicas: {{ .Values.replicaCount }}
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: nginx
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: nginx
    spec:
      containers:
        - name: nginx
          image: "{{ .Values.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.image.tag }}"
          ports:
            - containerPort: 80

Now we can do package our helm chart and install it.

helm package .

Successfully packaged chart and saved it to: /home/sher/Globallogic-assignment/nginx-helmchart/nginx-helmchart-0.1.0.tgz

helm install nginx-helmchart ./nginx-helmchart-0.1.0.tgz


Now we verify nginx deployment with the below commands.

kubectl get pods




